TABLE 1. Biometric data of
Hypselobarbus bicolor
from Sita River and Tunga River, Karnataka (Holotype: BNHS FWF 159 and Paratypes: ZSI/SRC F 8737, 3 ex.; ZSI/SRC F 8753, 1 ex. and MKC 405, 3 ex.)

subSubSection.paragraph:
Lateral line complete, with 34(2), 35(5) or 36(1) scales, plus 1(6) or 2(2) scales on caudal-fin base. Transverse scales from dorsal-fin origin to ventral-fin origin ½6/1/3½. Predorsal scales 11–12, circumpeduncular scales 14. Pelvic axillary scale present. Gill rakers simple, 4–6+11–12 on first gill arch; fifth ceratobranchial with 5+3+2 teeth, its proximal end curved (
Fig. 3
).
